    <sect1>
    <title>Non-free Software</title>

    <para>
    We don't recommend any of these propritary, non-free applications,
    but we want to replace all of them with open-source, free photo
    applications.  If you don't use the programs, feel free to ignore
    this part.
    </para>

      <sect2>
      <title>JCam</title>
      <para>
      Java application with support for several different cameras.
      This is a proprietary application, and as a result, has an approximate 
      $35 registration fee. The program stops working after the demo
      period has passed.
      </para><para><ulink url="http://www.jcam.com">http://www.jcam.com</ulink>
      </para>
      <para>Free software alternative: gPhoto <ulink url="http://www.gphoto.org">http://www.gphoto.org</ulink></para>
